			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1283">South Karana</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Aegis of Life as you should do it.</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Aegis of Life as you should do it.</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=476560"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:summoneaa@mail.com">Summoneaa Saindiva</a> | 
		                        8/3/2001 2:33:59 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Helo there friends.<BR>
This is one of the toughest &amp; most boring quests I have ever undertook, &amp; I'm telling you now, if you didnt even start on it yet, DON'T. There are now better items that are less involving to get &amp; have better stats than this NO DROP shiled. But, if you already started on it, or are locked up n it (the way I was, hehe) here are the steps as you should do them..<BR>
<BR>
1- What is the Aegis of Life: It's a Shield, equipale both on the Secondary and back slot (I have to warn you, you will not be able to bash wiht it if it's on your back!!) No Drop, Magic item, Lore Item. Stats are: Ac 12, Wis 10, Save versus Disease 25. Contains 1 charge of Superior Healing.<BR>
<BR>
2- Why would you quest for the AoL?: Well.. not sure actually. I was obsessed by it, wanted to have what we can call a &quot;Hard Quest Item&quot;, but realy, other than the stats, there is nothing appealing in it. (I still believe thoug that everey piece of nodrop item in this game is a piece in a biger quest yet to be discovered or implemented).<BR>
<BR>
3- What are the faction requirements to obtain the AoL: I heard &amp; read A LOT of times that you should have maximum PristsOfLife faction to be able to obtain the quest. I cant tell if less is required after the &quot;fixing&quot; they made to the quest though, as I was already maxed out when I did the quest (due to doing both Armor of Ro &amp; the Soulfire which requires Warmly faction with them, then the long nights and days awaiting Grimrot's spawn killing the putrid Skeletons in South Karana got me to Ally with them, then the sentence: &quot;Your faction standing with PriestsOfLife could not possibly get any better&quot;) So.. Whatever you do, pump that faction up. Kill bandits in WK &amp; return sashes, kill the royal fish in the pond &amp; return its corpse or simply donate 2cp at a time to the temple.. Any of these will do.. &amp; I might add as well killing putrids in SK.<BR>
<BR>
4- How to quest for the AoL:<BR>
Ok, the quest giver is Camlend Serbold. If you hail him he will tell you who he is &amp; what temple is he following.<BR>
Ask him: who is Lord Grimrot? &amp; he will answer that (If you have enough faction only) by telling you that he needed someone to bring him the heart and scythe of that Shadow Knights in the Karanas, &amp; that if you do, you will be rewarded.<BR>
So, If you do have MAXIMUM faction with PriestsOfLife, just head to SK, the skeletons camp at Location P14000, P1120 &amp; start camping the guy, if not, well.. look to step 3 above..:)<BR>
Now.. Grimrot have two forms (Live and Undead), both are Shadow Kights, both have pets &amp; you need to kill both in order to obtain both the LORE NODROP Pestilence Scythe and the LORE NO DROP Decaying Heart.<BR>
I referred to TONDS of posts, walkthroughs, friends' opinions as to how to get both versions to pop &amp; when, and the &quot;juice&quot; of this research is what follows:<BR>
Earlier, when the quest have been implemented, the place holder (a STANDING putrid Skeleton in the middle hutt of the camp) pops, then if you kill him at 5AM, after 3 RL hours another putrid will pop or the undead Grimrot. If you happen to leave the PH be &amp; decide not to kill it, it would depop after 6 EQ hours, then the Live Grimrot would pop after ONE RL HOUR of the depop. THIS NO LONGER HAPPENS. VI said in some patch that they &quot;fixed&quot; a bug concerning Lord Grimrot, well.. I was the depop thing, this was the main reason people always said that Live Grimrot is easier to get. Well, they are now even. The PH doesn't depop at all, you can leave it all you like, it will stay there until some whacko decides to kill it while you watch.<BR>
NOW, both Grimrots have an even chance to show after 3 RL hours to 216 minutes if you kill the placeholder at the &quot;right time&quot;, this chance is shared with the probability of another PH popping instead of Grimrot.<BR>
<BR>
a)- The Undead Grimrot: A level 30+ Skeleton Shadow Knight, with a Skeleton pet. he only pops at night time, so the trick is to kill the PH at a certain time so that the next spawn (after 3 hours to 216 minutes) is at NIGHT, the best time to get this one to pop is to kill the PH between 4 to 7 AM EQ time, then wait.. The next pop is GUARANTEED to be: another PH or Undead Grimrot. He drops the Decayed Heart and a droppable Pesttlence Scythe (THIS IS NOT THE SCYTHE YOU GIVE TO CAMLEND!!!!!)<BR>
<BR>
b)- The Live Grimrot: A level 35+ Human Shadow Knight, with a Skeleton pet. he only pops at day time, so the trick is to kill the PH at a certain time so that the next spawn (after 3 hours to 216 minutes) is at DAY, the best time to get this one to pop is to kill the PH between 4 to 7 PM EQ time, then wait.. The next pop is GUARANTEED to be: another PH or Live Grimrot. He drops two Pestilence Scythes, one of which is NO DROP, thus the one Calmend needs, the other one is mainly a toy, since it's worthless, but can be equipped for any class. I kept mine to amaze my friends (A paladin with a scythe..LOL).<BR>
<BR>
Now that you have both items, I suggest you scroll up to see the faction hits you had when killing the last Grimrot. If anything other than &quot;Your faction standing with PriestsOfLife could not possibly get any better&quot; then I strongly suggest that you work on faction again until it's maxed out. Even if Camlend considers you an ally &amp; have given you the quest!..<BR>
The camp for both Grimrots in itself is a PAIN, it took me one month to get Live Grimrot alone, including the last three days where i would kill the PH at 4-7 PM EQ time, log off then on after 3 hour to wait again for next pop, back to back, PH to PH for 72 hours, &amp; I still got EIGHT PHs IN A ROW before Live Grimrot decided to show his ugly face (&amp; got KS'd once by a Li'l halfling Cleric.. /grin)!!...<BR>
It's completely random, since a friend of mine got him to pop 2 times in a row the day before. SO.. you're not willing to take any chance or have your items eaten by Camlend, that's why you're going to HAVE to max your faction with PriestsOfLife in any way you like (Look step 3).<BR>
<BR>
When you head to Camlend, give him the items 1 at a time, &amp; he will reward you with this gold encrusted red beauty. It sheds light when equipped in secondary or on back slot (just like the CDS or Splitpaw mask), but you wont be able to bash with it unless it's in the secondary slot.<BR>
<BR>
I hope this helped a few of you get on the right path. Beware from higher levels that sit there &amp; dont respond your tells, they WILL KS the mob you've been camping for the last 216 RL minutes, so.. I suggest you dont do as I did (logged off after killing PH), just stand there, put AFK on, &amp; it would be better to have some friends with you when it's about to pop, not only because you might get KS'd but also because Live Grimrot is a real pain to kill if he got his humongous pet with him (&amp; he will summon it even if you're whacking on him in the mean time). The guy got me down to 2 bulbs of HP at L51, &amp; casts a weakening spell that got my str from 149 to 126.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck everybody, take care &amp; may Tunare be with you.<BR>
I will be posting a walkthrough about &quot;Divine Might as you should do it&quot; as soon as I get my screenshots &amp; logfile organized..:) /bow<BR>
<BR>
Summoneaa Saindiva<BR>
51st hand Cavalier of Tunare<BR>
Bertoxxulous Server
